article.headline: Gardner-Webb 66, Savannah St. 0
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. (AP) -- Stan Doolittle threw for 247 yards and four touchdowns in one half, and seven different players scored Saturday as Gardner-Webb ran up a 66-0 victory over Savannah State. The Bulldogs (5-4) set five school records, including most points in a game. They also set records with 607 yards of offense, 366 yards rushing, nine touchdowns and largest margin of victory. Savannah State (1-8) absorbed its second-worst loss in school history, eclipsed only by a 98-0 beating by Bethune-Cookman in 1953. Among those scoring for Gardner-Webb was defensive end Brian Johnston, who lined up at tight end and caught a 3-yard scoring pass with 30 seconds left in the first quarter. Gardner-Webb held Savannah State to 79 yards of offense, 22 of those on the ground.
